		"rdf:value": "Nicolae Roddy (personal communication, 2007) suggested “hierophagy”, which I have since adopted. Desroches (1973: 40 n.18) mentions the neologism, crediting F. A. Isambert (1966: 184), but the term does not occur in that publication of Isambert. See also Pfister (1948: 262), who simply defines hiero- phagy as a “sacral meal [which] represents the eating of the god or of the holy entity”. My use of the term here represents a significant development from these earlier brief allusions."
